From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 16:50:07 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 15/41] =?UTF-8?q?inline-3d(#625)=20B4d:=20GPU-resident=20w?=
 =?UTF-8?q?eave=20=E2=80=94=20skip=20the=20per-frame=20CPU=20readback=20(D?=
 =?UTF-8?q?Comp)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the DComp weave path's GPU->CPU->GPU sub-rect readback (SkSurface::readPixels /
Graphite asyncRescaleAndReadPixelsAndSubmit -> DisplayXRWeaveProvider::WeavePixels) with a
GPU-resident copy: the composited sub-rect is Skia-copied into an owned scratch
D3DImageBacking, its ID3D11Texture2D is obtained via ProduceOverlayForWeave, and
CopySubresourceRegion'd straight into the keyed-mutex weave input via the already-present
(previously dead) WeaveCanvas provider primitive. Eliminates the synchronous
compositor-GPU-thread readback stall — the real cost, which scales with the multi-element
spatial-desktop vision, not the ~7.6 MB.

WeaveCompositedSurface gains a prefer_zero_copy arg: true from MaybeWeaveRootRenderPass
(DComp root pass, D3D-backed), false from MaybeWeaveOutput (the GL
--disable-direct-composition path keeps the WeavePixels readback — the ANGLE backbuffer has
no extractable texture). Any zero-copy step failing falls back to WeavePixels for that rect
(still correct); the first fallback reason logs once at VLOG(1).

Two structural gotchas resolved under Graphite-Dawn:
- SCANOUT passes ProduceOverlay's manager gate but forces want_dcomp_texture
  (d3d_image_backing_factory.cc), so the overlay image is a DComp visual
  (kDCompVisualContent), not a raw texture. The scratch is therefore non-SCANOUT and read
  via ProduceOverlayForWeave — ProduceOverlay minus the SCANOUT enforcement — restored to
  SharedImageManager/RepresentationFactory (added in B2c.2 656af477, removed as dead code in
  B4b 14efab4d).
- A plain DISPLAY-only image is claimed by WrappedSkImageBackingFactory (no overlay) before
  D3DImageBackingFactory. Adding CPU_READ usage (in D3D's supported set, absent from
  WrappedSkImage's Graphite set and DComp's, and not a want_dcomp_texture trigger) routes the
  scratch to a plain, overlay-exposable D3DImageBacking (kD3D11Texture).

Validated on Leia (RTX 3080): DComp run logs "weave: GPU-resident scratch path (no CPU
readback)" + WeaveCanvas + service leia_dp_d3d11_process_atlas weave, zero 0x80070057, user
eyeball glasses-free 3D. GL run (--disable-direct-composition) unchanged: WeavePixels
fallback, GPU-resident marker + root-pass hook absent.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
